# Async Standup - Daily Summary Generator

Generate a standup summary by aggregating data from GitHub PRs, Linear issues, and Toggl time entries. Output to a temp file for copy-paste to Slack.

## Core Principles

1. **File-based output.** Always write to `.standup-YYYY-MM-DD.txt` in the current repo root. Never output the standup inline — the terminal reformats it and breaks Slack formatting.
2. **PRs are the unit of work, not commits.** Group everything by PR.
3. **Short descriptions.** 3-5 words max per item. Colleagues click the link if they want details.
4. **Link hygiene.** If a work item has a PR → link the PR only, never the Linear ID. If no PR → link the Linear issue URL. Never both.
5. **Read the actual reviews.** Don't trust `reviewDecision` — use `gh api` to read reviews, comments, and detect staleness.
6. **Deep Linear investigation.** Call `get_ticket` on every active issue to read descriptions and comments. The title alone misses critical context (spike PRs, decisions, blockers).
7. **Smart date range.** Monday standups cover Friday–Sunday. Other days cover since yesterday.
8. **Human tone.** Write like an engineer posting in Slack, not a report generator.

## Implementation

### Step 0: Create Output File

```bash
DATE=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)
STANDUP_FILE=".standup-${DATE}.txt"
```

All output goes into this file. Tell the user the file path at the end so they can copy it.

### Step 1: Gather Open PRs with Deep Analysis

**Get PR list:**
```bash
gh pr list --author=@me --state=open --json number,title,url,headRefName,reviewDecision,reviewRequests,isDraft,latestReviews,createdAt,updatedAt
```

**For each non-draft PR, analyze with `gh api`:**
```bash
# Reviews (approvals, changes requested)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/reviews --jq '.[] | {user: .user.login, state: .state, submitted_at: .submitted_at}'

# Latest commit (for staleness detection)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/commits --jq '.[-1] | {sha: .sha, date: .commit.committer.date}'

# Inline review comments (from reviewers, not bots)
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/comments --jq '.[] | select(.user.login != "Copilot" and (.user.login | test("bot") | not)) | {user: .user.login, body: .body[:150], path: .path}'

# Discussion comments
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues/{pr_number}/comments --jq '.[] | select(.user.login != "linear[bot]") | {user: .user.login, body: .body[:150]}'
```

**Staleness detection:** Compare latest commit date against each APPROVED review's `submitted_at`. If commit is newer → stale approval, needs re-review.

**Comment-but-no-decision detection:** If a reviewer left COMMENTED state (not APPROVED or CHANGES_REQUESTED), that's "reviewer commented, needs response" — different from "awaiting review".

### Step 2: Gather Recently Merged PRs

**Monday (cover Fri–Sun):**
```bash
gh pr list --author=@me --state=merged --json number,title,url,mergedAt,headRefName --limit 20
# Filter: mergedAt > Friday 00:00 UTC
```

**Other days (cover last 24h):**
```bash
gh pr list --author=@me --state=merged --json number,title,url,mergedAt,headRefName --limit 20
# Filter: mergedAt > yesterday 00:00 UTC
```

### Step 3: Deep Linear Investigation

**List active issues:**
```
linear_get_my_issues with state="active"
```

**For EVERY active issue, call `get_ticket`** to read:
- Full description (may reference PRs, spikes, design decisions)
- All comments (often contain links to upstream PRs, blockers, status updates)
- Sub-issues and their status

**Cross-reference:** Match Linear issues to PRs by branch name (e.g., `rafael/plt-672-...` maps to PLT-672). Issues with matching PRs don't need separate mention — the PR covers them.

**Also fetch Linear activity if possible** — recent issue updates, comments posted, status changes.

### Step 4: Gather Toggl Time (OPTIONAL)

```
toggl_get_time_entries with period="today"
```

Skip if no entries or user passes `--no-toggl`.

### Step 5: Write Standup to File

Use `[text](url)` for links — Slack's compose box renders these as clickable links.
Use `*bold*` for section headers — Slack renders this natively.
Use `:emoji_name:` for status icons.

**Format:**

```
:clipboard: *Standup — YYYY-MM-DD (Day)*

*Today*
• Merged [#39](url) — pod failure detection (fast-fail)
• Opened [#63](url) — dev env tooling rework
• Updated [#41](url) — pipeline diagnostics, needs re-review

*Open PRs:*
• [#63](url) Dev env tooling → reviewer :arrows_counterclockwise:
• [#41](url) Pipeline diagnostics → reviewer :warning: re-review needed
• [#13](url) Admin API + CLI → reviewer :arrows_counterclockwise: — reviewer2 commented on X
• [#62](url) Fix hardcoded values :memo: draft

*Up next:*
• Epic progress summary (N/M PRs merged, K remaining)
• [PLT-672](https://linear.app/metrevals/issue/PLT-672) Runner remote control — waiting on upstream
• Other planned work

*Needs attention:*
• [#13](url) open since Mar 24 — needs reviewer's review
• [PLT-696](https://linear.app/metrevals/issue/PLT-696) Red-team report — waiting on feedback
```

**Rules for each section:**

*Today:*
- One bullet per PR (merged, opened, updated)
- Description: 3-5 words, no technical details
- If a spike PR is on an external repo, link it with the repo name: `[inspect_ai #3599](url)`

*Open PRs:*
- `[#N](url) Short description → reviewer :status_icon:`
- If reviewer commented but didn't approve/reject, note what they commented on briefly
- Drafts at the bottom with `:memo: draft`

*Up next:*
- Work items NOT covered by open PRs
- Link Linear issues (not IDs) for items without PRs
- Epic summaries with progress counts

*Needs attention:*
- PRs that have been waiting too long for review
- Linear issues waiting on someone else's input
- Always link the item (PR or Linear URL)

### Step 6: Report to User

Tell the user:
```
Written to .standup-YYYY-MM-DD.txt — copy and paste to Slack.
Delete with: rm .standup-YYYY-MM-DD.txt
```

## Status Detection Logic

| Status | Icon | Detection |
|--------|------|-----------|
| Approved (fresh) | :white_check_mark: | APPROVED review, no commits since |
| Needs re-review | :warning: | APPROVED review but commits pushed AFTER approval |
| Changes requested | :warning: | Review state CHANGES_REQUESTED |
| Awaiting review | :arrows_counterclockwise: | Pending review requests, no blocking reviews |
| Reviewer commented | :speech_balloon: | COMMENTED state (not approved/rejected) — needs response |
| Draft | :memo: | `isDraft: true` |
| Blocked | :no_entry: | External dependency blocking progress |

## Anti-Patterns

1. **Don't output inline** — always write to file, terminal reformats everything
2. **Don't use `<url|text>` Slack API links** — they get `%7C`-encoded when pasting. Use `[text](url)`
3. **Don't list raw commits** — group by PR
4. **Don't include Linear ID when PR exists** — redundant clutter
5. **Don't write long descriptions** — 3-5 words, link has the details
6. **Don't trust `reviewDecision` alone** — read actual reviews via `gh api`
7. **Don't just list Linear titles** — call `get_ticket` to read comments and find hidden context
8. **Don't say "In Review"** — say WHO is reviewing and WHAT the actual status is
9. **Don't include both PR link and Linear link** — pick one (PR wins)

## Flags

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--date YYYY-MM-DD` | Generate for specific date |
| `--no-toggl` | Skip Toggl time tracking |
| `--no-linear` | Skip Linear issues |

